Product Information: The Barnes & Noble Nook Simple Touch is an e-reader for people who love reading but dont want to lug around heavy books. With the Nook, youll never have to worry about running out of great beach books while on vacation. If youre a student, you can say goodbye to backaches caused by carting around heavy textbooks in your backpack. The Barnes & Noble Nook Simple Touch weighs in at just 7.5 ounces, which is less than a paperback book.  At 5 inches by 5 inches by 7 inches, this Nook Simple Touch device is extremely thin. It slips easily into a purse, a backpack, or a jacket pocket, and you can upload up to 1,000 books, magazines, and newspapers into it. Its long-lasting battery allows you to read for weeks at a time on a single charge. If you want to increase the size of your portable library, simply add more memory. This Nook model comes with a 2GB hard drive, but you can add up to 32GB. Simply use the microSD slot on the right side of the unit to install your extra memory. Barnes & Noble is the worlds largest bookstore, so youll have access to more than two million titles. Most of these titles are available for less than physical copies, and thousands are actually free. Your Nook also enables you to borrow eBooks from your local public library. This e-reader relies on e-ink Pearl technology, which provides a contrast range thats 50% greater than its Nook predecessors. The contrast ratio is very close to what youll find in a paperback book. This results in sharper, more legible text on the screen so that youll be able to read more quickly with greater ease. Youll even be able to read books comfortably if youre sitting in bright sunlight. The Nook Simple Touch has a 6-inch display screen you can customize to match your reading preferences. With a touch of your finger, you can choose the font style thats easiest on your eyes and can use the touchscreen to make the text bigger or smaller. You can bookmark pages, highlight passages you may want to remember, and look up unfamiliar words as well. The Nook Touch reader uses an Android operating system and has built-in support for Wi-Fi. Some Nook owners use this Wi-Fi capability to customize their devices with apps and games. If you want to connect to an external Wi-Fi network, a browser page will pop up, allowing you to sign on. The Nook Simple Touch reader is an attractive matte black, and its ergonomically designed to balance easily in one hand. Turn it on and off using the power button, which is located on the top of the back of the unit. Toward the bottom of the back is the USB port thats used to charge the unit. The USB port can also be used to transfer content from your computer. The buttons on either side of the N insignia at the bottom of the Nooks front are for turning pages. The Barnes & Noble Nook Simple Touch is a wonderful device for anyone who loves tablets but also loves reading books.

Product Information: The Amazon Kindle Touch 4th generation lets users keep every e-book in their libraries accessible and organized with the touch of a finger. This sleek tablet e-reader offers users the ability to navigate the Amazon library easily using a convenient touch screen. Just tap an area at the top of the screen to open up the menu. This Amazon Touch stores up to 3,000 books or about 4GB of data, and users receive free cloud storage for all Amazon content. To purchase more books for your Kindle e-reader, simply type the title or author into the Amazon search bar, purchase, and upload the reading material to the Kindle. The Kindle Touch is completely wireless, allowing you to download books and magazines over Wi-Fi without needing to use a laptop or desktop computer. This version of the Amazon Kindle Touch features a 6-inch touchscreen that is glare free. This feature allows it to be used on the beach, at the park, and in other conditions where bright light may be a problem. The Amazon Kindle is designed specifically with the user in mind, featuring innovative E Ink technology that is easy on the eyes. Kindles e-readers use a proprietary E-ink Pearl technology that includes hand-built fonts and actual ink particles. Featuring a 167 ppi display with a 16-level gray scale, the Amazon Kindle provides users with consistently excellent image quality. The screen features a uniform contrast ratio, which ensures that the screen looks the same at any angle. This product also features a 100 percent aperture ratio that provides sharp image quality.The Kindle Touch doesn't require power to display a page of text, so a single charge can last for up to six weeks. This means you can read a book cover to cover without having to worry about needing to charge the device. When your battery does run low, simply use the included USB 2.0 charging cord. In approximately four hours, your Amazon Kindle is fully charged and ready to go again. The Kindle Touch is perfect for users who are always on the go. At just 6.7 ounces, this compact e-reader weighs less than a single paperback book and has enough storage capacity to hold thousands of titles. This Kindle is comfortable to hold in the palm of your hand for extended periods of time, and it's easy to flip pages with a simple tap. This model of Kindle is designed specifically for a pure reading experience without the distraction of texts, social media notifications, video, or alerts. Readers looking for a Wi-Fi device that provides an experience as close as possible to that of a physical book should consider Kindle Touch e-readers. Both casual users and avid readers benefit from buying this simple and versatile reader. Available accessories for this unit include a fitted cover, black leather case, or convenient external light. This is a versatile, compact tablet that makes your reading experience even easier.

Product Information: The third generation version of the Amazon Kindle features a 6 inch screen, a keyboard, and 4G capabilities. This model of Kindle is Wi-Fi enabled to let you browse and shop for e-books. When you want to find an e-book, searching can be easy. This reader will load any electronic book that you purchased through your past Kindles, and you can view all the content and the cover of each e-book on the display. In addition to instant downloads that are sold in the Kindle store, you can also search for e-books from your library. This product can allow you to borrow digital books from your own library account. You can even use the Kindle's recommendations after you rank the book you have just finished reading.  This Amazon Kindle has a roomy memory so you can store many ebooks from the sellers you love at once. With 4GB of hard drive space, it can hold up to 3,500 e-books. You can sort your books by author, genre, date loaded, or subject. This can make it easy to find your collections. As you start typing on the keyboard, it begins to offer selections based on your content. The tablets also remember your past searches. The keyboard is in a QWERTY style. If you need to access numbers, the shift key allows you to access those as well as special characters. If you like audio books, this keyboard features a text to speech function. There is a standard 3.5 mm headphone jack.  The screen provides greater contrast than earlier Kindles, making it easier to see. You can take it outside and read in bright sunlight without any glare on the screen. When you are using it before bed, you can dim the screen to make it easier on your eyes. In addition to adjusting the brightness of this Kindle, you can also change its type size. This can allow young readers to focus on the words and far sighted people to read without glasses or eyestrain. The 6 inch display size can allow you to read several paragraphs of text in the standard size. The Kindle uses e-ink and has 167 pixels per inch.  The battery on the third generation Kindle is long lasting, which can provide up to a month of reading time before you have to check for a recharge. With the Wi-Fi shut off, the Amazon Kindle can stay charged for up to six weeks. You can recharge this device with your laptop or desktop computer. It also comes with its own charging cable and charger that you can plug into any outlet. The microUSB charging cable measures 36 inches long, lies flat and is tangle free. The bottom edge of the device features a helpful indicator light to let you know when it needs to be charged. When the light turns red, it is time to charge the tablet. This Wi-Fi tablet measures 8 inches long, 5.3 inches wide, and 0.4 inches thick. The devices weigh 10.2 ounces. The lightweight reader can easily tuck right into a bag or large pocket, even when you've added a protective cover to it. The back of the device is rubberized, which can make it easy to grip. You can enjoy the pleasure of reading with the ample screen space and helpful keyboard on this Amazon Kindle.

Product Information: The Barnes & Noble Nook Simple Touch is an e-reader for people who love reading but dont want to lug around heavy books. With the Nook, youll never have to worry about running out of great beach books while on vacation. If youre a student, you can say goodbye to backaches caused by carting around heavy textbooks in your backpack. The Barnes & Noble Nook Simple Touch weighs in at just 7.5 ounces, which is less than a paperback book.  At 5 inches by 5 inches by 7 inches, this Nook Simple Touch device is extremely thin. It slips easily into a purse, a backpack, or a jacket pocket, and you can upload up to 1,000 books, magazines, and newspapers into it. Its long-lasting battery allows you to read for weeks at a time on a single charge. If you want to increase the size of your portable library, simply add more memory. This Nook model comes with a 2GB hard drive, but you can add up to 32GB. Simply use the microSD slot on the right side of the unit to install your extra memory. Barnes & Noble is the worlds largest bookstore, so youll have access to more than two million titles. Most of these titles are available for less than physical copies, and thousands are actually free. Your Nook also enables you to borrow eBooks from your local public library. This e-reader relies on e-ink Pearl technology, which provides a contrast range thats 50% greater than its Nook predecessors. The contrast ratio is very close to what youll find in a paperback book. This results in sharper, more legible text on the screen so that youll be able to read more quickly with greater ease. Youll even be able to read books comfortably if youre sitting in bright sunlight. The Nook Simple Touch has a 6-inch display screen you can customize to match your reading preferences. With a touch of your finger, you can choose the font style thats easiest on your eyes and can use the touchscreen to make the text bigger or smaller. You can bookmark pages, highlight passages you may want to remember, and look up unfamiliar words as well. The Nook Touch reader uses an Android operating system and has built-in support for Wi-Fi. Some Nook owners use this Wi-Fi capability to customize their devices with apps and games. If you want to connect to an external Wi-Fi network, a browser page will pop up, allowing you to sign on. The Nook Simple Touch reader is an attractive matte black, and its ergonomically designed to balance easily in one hand. Turn it on and off using the power button, which is located on the top of the back of the unit. Toward the bottom of the back is the USB port thats used to charge the unit. The USB port can also be used to transfer content from your computer. The buttons on either side of the N insignia at the bottom of the Nooks front are for turning pages. The Barnes & Noble Nook Simple Touch is a wonderful device for anyone who loves tablets but also loves reading books.

Product Information: The Barnes & Noble Nook Simple Touch is an e-reader for people who love reading but dont want to lug around heavy books. With the Nook, youll never have to worry about running out of great beach books while on vacation. If youre a student, you can say goodbye to backaches caused by carting around heavy textbooks in your backpack. The Barnes & Noble Nook Simple Touch weighs in at just 7.5 ounces, which is less than a paperback book.  At 5 inches by 5 inches by 7 inches, this Nook Simple Touch device is extremely thin. It slips easily into a purse, a backpack, or a jacket pocket, and you can upload up to 1,000 books, magazines, and newspapers into it. Its long-lasting battery allows you to read for weeks at a time on a single charge. If you want to increase the size of your portable library, simply add more memory. This Nook model comes with a 2GB hard drive, but you can add up to 32GB. Simply use the microSD slot on the right side of the unit to install your extra memory. Barnes & Noble is the worlds largest bookstore, so youll have access to more than two million titles. Most of these titles are available for less than physical copies, and thousands are actually free. Your Nook also enables you to borrow eBooks from your local public library. This e-reader relies on e-ink Pearl technology, which provides a contrast range thats 50% greater than its Nook predecessors. The contrast ratio is very close to what youll find in a paperback book. This results in sharper, more legible text on the screen so that youll be able to read more quickly with greater ease. Youll even be able to read books comfortably if youre sitting in bright sunlight. The Nook Simple Touch has a 6-inch display screen you can customize to match your reading preferences. With a touch of your finger, you can choose the font style thats easiest on your eyes and can use the touchscreen to make the text bigger or smaller. You can bookmark pages, highlight passages you may want to remember, and look up unfamiliar words as well. The Nook Touch reader uses an Android operating system and has built-in support for Wi-Fi. Some Nook owners use this Wi-Fi capability to customize their devices with apps and games. If you want to connect to an external Wi-Fi network, a browser page will pop up, allowing you to sign on. The Nook Simple Touch reader is an attractive matte black, and its ergonomically designed to balance easily in one hand. Turn it on and off using the power button, which is located on the top of the back of the unit. Toward the bottom of the back is the USB port thats used to charge the unit. The USB port can also be used to transfer content from your computer. The buttons on either side of the N insignia at the bottom of the Nooks front are for turning pages. The Barnes & Noble Nook Simple Touch is a wonderful device for anyone who loves tablets but also loves reading books.

Product Information: If you love reading, then the Sony PRS-505 eBook Reader has much to offer. This digital device gives you the ability to store hundreds of eBooks on the internal storage space. You also have the option of using compatible memory cards and flash drives for storing more books as well. The Sony PRS-505 eBook Reader supports a multitude of data formats. Enjoy eBooks, files, and documents that are written in BBeB, DRM, DOC, PDF, RTF, and TXT format. The generously sized screen offers clarity and minimizes eyestrain for all of your mobile reading pleasures.  A single core 800 Hz Celeron processor delivers the speed capabilities of the Sony PRS-505 eBook Reader. This processor has 128MB of onboard RAM that offers 256MB of internal memory space. This offers a generous amount of storage space for storing all of your eBooks. There are two expansion slots designed into the Sony PRS-505 model eBook Reader. They include a SD memory card slot and a memory stick PRO Duo slot that increases the books you are able to access at any given time. A USB port is built into the eBook reader, allowing you to connect to compatible electronic devices such as tablets, laptops, desktop computers, and smartphones for rapid transfer of files. Use the USB port as a means for keeping the device charged at all times.  The portable Sony PRS505 eBook Reader does have a Sony Reader Software operating system pre-installed on the hard drive. This operating system gives you the freedom to download eBooks from the Sony Online Store. You can also purchase certain software and accessories that expands the amount of enjoyment you experience while reading on the go.  View all of your eBooks on the 6-inch E Ink display screen. This screen offers a monochrome color scheme display that features 8 grayscale levels. With a 600 by 800-pixel display, the resolution all of your content comes across with clarity.  The wireless Sony Reader PRS-505 model does have audio playback functions and capabilities. The device supports both AAC and MP3 formats. A photo viewer is also built into the e-Book reader. Enjoy the ability to view photos and pictures that are set to BMP, GIF, JPEG, and PNG formats.  A non-removable Lithium-ion battery provides all of the power needed for your Sony Digital eBook Reader. This battery life delivers 7500-pages worth of charge and will last approximately four hours between charging. You have the option to keep the battery charged by connecting the included USB cable to a compatible PC USB port.  The PC that is used to connect with these wireless Sony Reader devices should operate on one of: Microsoft Windows Vista, Microsoft Windows Vista Business, Microsoft Windows XP Professional, Microsoft Windows Vista Home Basic, Microsoft Windows Vista Ultimate, Microsoft Windows XP, Microsoft Windows XP Home Edition, or Microsoft Windows XP Media Center Edition OS.  The portable Sony PRS-505 Digital eBook Reader does come with an outer cover. This protects the device from dirt, dust, and other elements when not in use. Available accessories are proper sized screen protectors to prevent against scratches and marring that can distort your viewing on the Sony Reader while reading on the go.

This e-reader relies on e-ink Pearl technology, which provides a contrast range thats 50% greater than its Nook predecessors. The Nook Simple Touch reader is an attractive matte black, and its ergonomically designed to balance easily in one hand. When you close it, the cover protects the screen from scratches. When opened again, the covers offer you a choice between a keyboard and a multitouch touch pad. Each cover comes with a gyroscope and an accelerometer sensor to know when the cover has been flipped around. This allows it to disable the keys or touch pad to avoid accidental commands.  On the right side of the Surface Pro, there is a full size USB 3.0 port, an HDMI Micro port, a dock connector port, and a magnetic charging port or microUSB. Also included is a microSDXC card slot, which allows you to add additional memory up to 200GB. The Pro comes with a 42W lithium-ion battery for a long lasting charge. For a unique take on a tablet/laptop 2 in 1 device, you can pick up a Microsoft Surface Pro.

Weighing in at only 1.76 pounds, Microsoft Surface tablets are ideal options for hands-on operations involving graphic design or other professional work. Product Information: The Barnes & Noble Nook Simple Touch is an e-reader for people who love reading but dont want to lug around heavy books. With the Nook, youll never have to worry about running out of great beach books while on vacation. If youre a student, you can say goodbye to backaches caused by carting around heavy textbooks in your backpack. The Barnes & Noble Nook Simple Touch weighs in at just 7.5 ounces, which is less than a paperback book.  At 5 inches by 5 inches by 7 inches, this Nook Simple Touch device is extremely thin. It slips easily into a purse, a backpack, or a jacket pocket, and you can upload up to 1,000 books, magazines, and newspapers into it. Its long-lasting battery allows you to read for weeks at a time on a single charge. If you want to increase the size of your portable library, simply add more memory. This Nook model comes with a 2GB hard drive, but you can add up to 32GB. Simply use the microSD slot on the right side of the unit to install your extra memory. Barnes & Noble is the worlds largest bookstore, so youll have access to more than two million titles. Most of these titles are available for less than physical copies, and thousands are actually free. Your Nook also enables you to borrow eBooks from your local public library. This e-reader relies on e-ink Pearl technology, which provides a contrast range thats 50% greater than its Nook predecessors. The contrast ratio is very close to what youll find in a paperback book. This results in sharper, more legible text on the screen so that youll be able to read more quickly with greater ease. Youll even be able to read books comfortably if youre sitting in bright sunlight. The Nook Simple Touch has a 6-inch display screen you can customize to match your reading preferences. With a touch of your finger, you can choose the font style thats easiest on your eyes and can use the touchscreen to make the text bigger or smaller. You can bookmark pages, highlight passages you may want to remember, and look up unfamiliar words as well. The Nook Touch reader uses an Android operating system and has built-in support for Wi-Fi. Some Nook owners use this Wi-Fi capability to customize their devices with apps and games. If you want to connect to an external Wi-Fi network, a browser page will pop up, allowing you to sign on. The Nook Simple Touch reader is an attractive matte black, and its ergonomically designed to balance easily in one hand. Turn it on and off using the power button, which is located on the top of the back of the unit. Toward the bottom of the back is the USB port thats used to charge the unit. The USB port can also be used to transfer content from your computer. The buttons on either side of the N insignia at the bottom of the Nooks front are for turning pages. The Barnes & Noble Nook Simple Touch is a wonderful device for anyone who loves tablets but also loves reading books.

The manufacturer has included some exclusive apps, and you can connect easily to the Google Play store to download your favorites. The Google productivity suite, which includes Gmail, Gchat, Google Drive and Google Office, is pre-installed. The Chrome browser is built in, although Samsung has provided a default browser if preferred. Users can type in information or check their messages using either the Samsung or Google built-in keyboard programs. The tablet is compatible with third party virtual and physical keyboards. This enables the Samsung Galaxy Tab to function as a desktop replacement device if needed.

Product Information: The Barnes & Noble Nook Simple Touch is an e-reader for people who love reading but dont want to lug around heavy books. With the Nook, youll never have to worry about running out of great beach books while on vacation. If youre a student, you can say goodbye to backaches caused by carting around heavy textbooks in your backpack. The Barnes & Noble Nook Simple Touch weighs in at just 7.5 ounces, which is less than a paperback book.  At 5 inches by 5 inches by 7 inches, this Nook Simple Touch device is extremely thin. It slips easily into a purse, a backpack, or a jacket pocket, and you can upload up to 1,000 books, magazines, and newspapers into it. Its long-lasting battery allows you to read for weeks at a time on a single charge. If you want to increase the size of your portable library, simply add more memory. This Nook model comes with a 2GB hard drive, but you can add up to 32GB. Simply use the microSD slot on the right side of the unit to install your extra memory. Barnes & Noble is the worlds largest bookstore, so youll have access to more than two million titles. Most of these titles are available for less than physical copies, and thousands are actually free. Your Nook also enables you to borrow eBooks from your local public library. This e-reader relies on e-ink Pearl technology, which provides a contrast range thats 50% greater than its Nook predecessors. The contrast ratio is very close to what youll find in a paperback book. This results in sharper, more legible text on the screen so that youll be able to read more quickly with greater ease. Youll even be able to read books comfortably if youre sitting in bright sunlight. The Nook Simple Touch has a 6-inch display screen you can customize to match your reading preferences. With a touch of your finger, you can choose the font style thats easiest on your eyes and can use the touchscreen to make the text bigger or smaller. You can bookmark pages, highlight passages you may want to remember, and look up unfamiliar words as well. The Nook Touch reader uses an Android operating system and has built-in support for Wi-Fi. Some Nook owners use this Wi-Fi capability to customize their devices with apps and games. If you want to connect to an external Wi-Fi network, a browser page will pop up, allowing you to sign on. The Nook Simple Touch reader is an attractive matte black, and its ergonomically designed to balance easily in one hand. Turn it on and off using the power button, which is located on the top of the back of the unit. Toward the bottom of the back is the USB port thats used to charge the unit. The USB port can also be used to transfer content from your computer. The buttons on either side of the N insignia at the bottom of the Nooks front are for turning pages. The Barnes & Noble Nook Simple Touch is a wonderful device for anyone who loves tablets but also loves reading books.
